wishingstar.desc: A stone found in the Galar region with a mysterious power. It’s said that your dreams come true if you find one.

dynamaxband.name: Dynamax Band
dynamaxband.desc: A Wishing Star has been affixed to it. It lets out a light that allows Pokémon to Dynamax when at a Power Spot.

fishingrodgalar.desc: Use it by the water to fish up various kinds of Pokémon.

rotombike.name: Rotom Bike
rotombike.desc: This bike can be combined with the Pokémon Rotom to use a turbo boost.

sausages.name: Sausages
sausages.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. These sausages should be boiled before eating.

bobsfoodtin.name: Bob’s Food Tin
bobsfoodtin.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. The tinned food that Bob sells is curiously popular in Galar.

bachsfoodtin.name: Bach’s Food Tin
bachsfoodtin.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. The tinned food that Bach sells is curiously popular in Galar.

tinofbeans.name: Tin of Beans
tinofbeans.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. When simmered, the beans suffuse a dish with their mild flavor.

bread.name: Bread
bread.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. An indispensable tool for mopping up that extra curry left on your plate.

pasta.name: Pasta
pasta.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. These flour noodles make for a surprisingly good match with curry.

mixedmushrooms.name: Mixed Mushrooms
mixedmushrooms.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. The chewy texture of the mushrooms transforms any dish they’re added to.

smokepoketail.name: Smoke-Poke Tail
smokepoketail.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. When a Slowpoke’s tail falls off, it grows back quickly.

largeleek.name: Large Leek
largeleek.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. Whether this is the kind of vegetable stalk that Farfetch’d like is unknown.

fancyapple.name: Fancy Apple
fancyapple.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. An apple chosen above others. It has spectacular form and a brilliant sheen.

brittlebones.name: Brittle Bones
brittlebones.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. The taste boiled off from the bones is sure to give a dish a light umami taste.

packofpotatoes.name: Pack of Potatoes
packofpotatoes.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. Potatoes help mellow out a spicy taste, to make a dish more mild.

pungentroot.name: Pungent Root
pungentroot.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. Though carelessly picked, these herbs can add a fragrant accent to a dish.

saladmix.name: Salad Mix
saladmix.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. The assortment of vegetables looks quite appealing and healthy.

friedfood.name: Fried Food
friedfood.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. It’s been a while since it was fried, so it’s gotten greasy.

boiledegg.name: Boiled Egg
boiledegg.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. Even just one boiled egg can really enhance a dish.

campinggear.name: Camping Gear
campinggear.desc: Everything you need to set up a tent and get cooking in a Wild Area or at a camping spot.

hitechearbuds.name: Hi-tech Earbuds
hitechearbuds.desc: Strange earbuds that allow you to freely control the volume of various sounds.

fruitbunch.name: Fruit Bunch
fruitbunch.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. The syrupy fruits give off a strong tropical feel.

moomoocheese.name: Moomoo Cheese
moomoocheese.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. Melted cheese can really give a curry some richness.

spicemix.name: Spice Mix
spicemix.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. There are over fifty spices contained within this ingredient’s hot flavor.

freshcream.name: Fresh Cream
freshcream.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. Add some whipped cream to a spicy curry to give it some sweetness.

packagedcurry.name: Packaged Curry
packagedcurry.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. Using packaged curry helps make sure there are no slipups when cooking.

coconutmilk.name: Coconut Milk
coconutmilk.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. The refined sweetness of this coconut milk makes it quite popular.

instantnoodles.name: Instant Noodles
instantnoodles.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. It has a junk-food sort of taste, but it goes well with curry.

precookedburger.name: Precooked Burger
precookedburger.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. If you’re unsure about what to cook, you can’t go wrong with some burger.

gigantamix.name: Gigantamix
gigantamix.desc: One of the many ingredients that can be used for cooking at your camp. A mysterious spice. Even a tiny sprinkle is sure to make a curry gigantic.

wishingchip.name: Wishing Chip
wishingchip.desc: Toss a number of them into a Pokémon Den for the chance to attract a wild Dynamax Pokémon.

rotombikewatermode.name: Rotom Bike
rotombikewatermode.desc: This bike can be combined with the Pokémon Rotom to not only do a turbo boost but also run on the water.

catchingcharm.name: Catching Charm
catchingcharm.desc: Holding it is said to increase the chance of getting a critical catch. Curiously, the charm doesn’t shake much.

oldletter.name: Old Letter
oldletter.desc: A letter entrusted to you by a girl, to be delivered to a boy. Strangely, it looks old to you.

bandautograph.name: Band Autograph
bandautograph.desc: It’s signed by all members of the Galar region’s most charismatic band, the Maximizers.

soniasbook.name: Sonia’s Book
soniasbook.desc: Professor Sonia’s published writings. Her new discoveries about the Galar region’s legends are recorded in this enjoyable read.

rotomcatalog.name: Rotom Catalog
rotomcatalog.desc: A catalog of devices that Rotom like. Use the catalog to have Rotom hop in and out of the various devices listed within.

maxhoney.name: Max Honey
maxhoney.desc: Honey that Dynamax Vespiquen produces. Adding this honey to Max Soup makes the taste very smooth. It also has the same effect as a Max Revive.

maxmushrooms.name: Max Mushrooms
maxmushrooms.desc: Mushrooms that have the power of changing Dynamax forms. They boost all stats of a Pokémon during battle.

galaricatwig.name: Galarica Twig
galaricatwig.desc: A twig from a species of tree called Galarica that grows in certain areas around the Galar region. It’s a material for an accessory for a certain Pokémon.

stylecard.name: Style Card
stylecard.desc: A card that increases the selection in boutiques and hair salons.

armorpass.name: Armor Pass
armorpass.desc: A pass to go to the Isle of Armor. Show it to the rail staff at Wedgehurst Station.

rotombikesparklingwhite.name: Rotom Bike
rotombikesparklingwhite.desc: This bike can do a turbo boost and run on the water using Rotom’s power. It’s a sparkling white that shines brilliantly.

rotombikeglisteningblack.name: Rotom Bike
rotombikeglisteningblack.desc: This bike can do a turbo boost and run on the water using Rotom’s power. It’s a glistening black that shines reddish-black.

expcharm.name: Exp. Charm
expcharm.desc: A charm that increases the Exp. Points that Pokémon can get. A machine-like object is inside the charm.

armoriteore.name: Armorite Ore
armoriteore.desc: Rare ore that can be obtained on the Isle of Armor. Something good will happen if you give it to a collector on the Isle of Armor.

markcharm.name: Mark Charm
markcharm.desc: A mysterious and unique charm that increases the chance of finding a Pokémon with a mark.

reinsofunitymerge.name: Reins of Unity
reinsofunitymerge.desc: Reins that people presented to the king. They enhance Calyrex’s power over bountiful harvests and unite Calyrex with its beloved steed.

reinsofunitysplit.name: Reins of Unity
reinsofunitysplit.desc: Reins that people presented to the king. They enable those who are connected to communicate with each other. The reins separate Calyrex and its beloved steed.

legendaryclue1.name: Legendary Clue 1
legendaryclue1.desc: A clue about the King of Bountiful Harvests. It’s written by Peony, and an old photo is attached to it.

legendaryclue2.name: Legendary Clue 2
legendaryclue2.desc: A clue about the legend of giants. It’s written by Peony and has unique drawings.

legendaryclue3.name: Legendary Clue 3
legendaryclue3.desc: A clue about the legend of bird Pokémon. It’s written by Peony and has a unique drawing.

legendarycluequestion.name: Legendary Clue?
legendarycluequestion.desc: A mysterious clue that Peony seems to have dropped. There’s a photo attached to it showing a shining hole opening above the Max Lair.

crownpass.name: Crown Pass
crownpass.desc: A pass to go to the Crown Tundra. Show it to the rail staff at Wedgehurst Station.

woodencrown.name: Wooden Crown
woodencrown.desc: A mysterious object made of wood. Part of it seems to be chipped. Maybe it’s meant to be part of something.

radiantpetal.name: Radiant Petal
radiantpetal.desc: A single petal that the King of Bountiful Harvests gave you. It radiates faint light.

whitemanehair.name: White Mane Hair
whitemanehair.desc: Mane hair that belonged to the King of Bountiful Harvests’ beloved steed, Glastrier. The hair is strong and very flexible.

blackmanehair.name: Black Mane Hair
blackmanehair.desc: Mane hair that belonged to the King of Bountiful Harvests’ beloved steed, Spectrier. The hair is very smooth to the touch.

icerootcarrot.name: Iceroot Carrot
icerootcarrot.desc: Produce that the King of Bountiful Harvests’ beloved steed likes to eat. It grew in a field covered in snow.

shaderootcarrot.name: Shaderoot Carrot
shaderootcarrot.desc: Produce that the King of Bountiful Harvests’ beloved steed likes to eat. It grew in a gloomy field.

dyniteore.name: Dynite Ore
dyniteore.desc: Mysterious ore that can be obtained in the Max Lair. Something good will happen if you give it to a collector in the Crown Tundra.

carrotseeds.name: Carrot Seeds
carrotseeds.desc: Seeds to plant in a field. The kind of carrot you’ll get is determined by which field you plant the seeds in.

abilitypatch.name: Ability Patch
abilitypatch.desc: A patch that allows a Pokémon with a regular Ability to have a rare Ability.

reinsofunity.name: Reins of Unity
reinsofunity.desc: Cords that shine when you hold them up to the light. The people of old times presented these to the King of Bountiful Harvests to express their gratitude.

linkingcord.name: Linking Cord
linkingcord.desc: Allows a Pokemon whose evolution is usually triggered by trading to evolve

laheavyball.name: Heavy Ball
laheavyball.desc: Doesn't fly far, but is more effective if the Pokémon hasn't noticed the player.

laleadenball.name: Leaden Ball
laleadenball.desc: Upgraded version of the Heavy Ball. Doesn't fly far, but is more effective if the Pokémon hasn't noticed the player.

lagigatonball.name: Gigaton Ball
lagigatonball.desc: Upgraded version of the Leaden Ball. Doesn't fly far, but is more effective if the Pokémon hasn't noticed the player.

lafeatherball.name: Feather Ball
lafeatherball.desc: Can be thrown further than a regular Poké Ball. Is more effective for catching Pokémon that fly high in the air.

lawingball.name: Wing Ball
lawingball.desc: Can be thrown further than a Feather Ball. Is more effective for catching Pokémon that fly high in the air.

lajetball.name: Jet Ball
lajetball.desc: Can be thrown further than a Wing Ball. Is more effective for catching Pokémon that fly high in the air.
